description:
The Production Process of Korean Hairdressing Scissors Made with 0.01mm Extreme Precision

This video documents the production process behind the multi-purpose Korean hairdressing scissors we use so casually in everyday life.
Despite their small size, these scissors must deliver powerful cutting performance,
requiring numerous precise steps and meticulous craftsmanship throughout the entire manufacturing process.
The company featured in this video, Buhung Industry, has been producing beauty and grooming tools since 1969.
With over 50 years of accumulated technology and expertise,
they have partnered with both domestic and international brands such as Three Seven (777), Bell Metal, and Royal Metal,
maintaining one of the highest quality standards in Korea for nail-care and beauty accessories.
Join us as we explore how these Korean hairdressing scissors are carefully crafted from start to finish.
